  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in the vast majority of jurisdictions worldwide. It involves the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. The intent is to make the money appear as though it comes from a legitimate source. Laws against money laundering are in place to combat organized crime, corruption, terrorism, and other illegal activities, as they help prevent criminals from profiting from and expanding their operations with illicit funds. Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including heavy fines and imprisonment.",
